2. Introduction
This is a simple chatbot I made using 2 of my cousins(Hiba for Hibatron Rosheen for Rosh2D2 ), by recording their responses and using those as the answers of the chatbot, Ive put in multiple "out of the ordinary questions" in here and easter eggs that the user can ask and have fun with. Try asking who the strongest bot is, or how to lose weight..
________________________________________
3. Problem Statement
Heres a simple project that demonstrates core concepts without requiring complex algorithms. Traditional chatbot examples can be repetitive or overly advanced. This project solves that by creating a lightweight, creative chatbot that showcases rule based responses, multiple personas, and randomized outputs.
________________________________________
4. Functional Requirements
1.	Accept user input via command line.
2.	Respond to greetings with randomized persona specific replies.
3.	Provide jokes when prompted with the keyword “joke.”
4.	Answer simple queries such as “how are you” or “strongest robot.”
5.	Offer randomized fallback responses when input does not match any rule.
6.	Exit gracefully when the user types “bye.”
________________________________________
5. Non Functional Requirements
•	Usability: Simple and intuitive for beginners.
•	Reliability: Consistent responses without crashing.
•	Maintainability: Easy to extend with new rules and responses.
•	Performance: Fast response time with minimal resource usage.
•	Portability: Runs on any system with Python 3.x installed.
________________________________________
6. System Architecture
The chatbot follows a simple architecture:
•	Input Layer: Accepts user text input.
•	Processing Layer: Matches input against predefined rules and selects responses.
•	Randomization Module: Chooses a random response from available options.
•	Output Layer: Displays the chatbot’s reply in the terminal.
(Insert a block diagram here with arrows showing Input → Processing → Output.)
