________________________________________
11. Testing Approach
•	Unit Testing: Verified each intent (greeting, joke, query, fallback, exit).
•	Functional Testing: Ensured chatbot responds correctly to expected inputs.
•	Boundary Testing: Checked behavior with unexpected inputs (nonsense text).
•	Exit Testing: Confirmed chatbot terminates correctly when “bye” is entered.
________________________________________
12. Challenges Faced
•	Handling multiple responses without repetition.
•	Ensuring proper indentation and syntax in Python.
•	Managing response lists with commas and formatting.
•	Balancing humor with professionalism in chatbot replies.
________________________________________
13. Learnings & Key Takeaways
•	Gained practical experience in Python programming.
•	Understood rule based AI systems and their limitations.
•	Learned how randomness can improve user experience.
•	Realized the importance of clean code and documentation.
